[Data by country, area, or territory for 27 Dec 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20DEC27_1640721941.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 31.8% of cases and 5.4% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 101.37 million cases. The USA reported 95 518 cases over the last 24 hours. An additional 7 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Argentina, Mexico, Peru, Colombia, Chile, Puerto Rico, and Bolivia).

- The European region reported 46.7% of daily case numbers and 68% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 97.54 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include the UK, Spain, Belgium, Sweden, and Switzerland, among others. A total of 15 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, with 8 reporting more than 10 000, 8 reporting over 1000 cases, and an additional 8 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 2.7% of daily case numbers and 5.3% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 17.1 million cases. Iran (1857) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by UAE (1803), Jordan (1447) and Lebanon (1311). Morocco, Egypt and Libya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 7.7% of daily case numbers and 2.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 7.08 million cases. Mozambique (6640) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by South Africa (5603), Ethiopia (2946), Ghana (1881), Uganda (1859), Nigeria (1547), Zambia (1539), Kenya (1196), and Namibia (1053). Burundi, Zimbabwe, Lesotho, Congo, and Gabon reported more than 500, but less than 1000 cases over the last 24 hours. A total of 14 countries/ territories did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 8.4% of daily case numbers and 8.5% deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 11.09 million cases. Vietnam (15 218) reported the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by Australia, South Korea, Malaysia, and Lao PDR.

- The South East Asia region reported 2.4% of the daily newly reported cases and 9.5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 44.90 million cases. India is dominant, reporting 6531 cases during the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (2437). Bangladesh (373), Nepal (251), Myanmar (200), and Indonesia (120) all reported less than 500 cases over the last 24 hours. Sri Lanka, and Maldives, among others, did not report cases over the last many days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 27 Dec 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

